{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/Beaglebone-getting-started-p2","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>As you recall from pt. 1 of this series, we installed an OS on the Beaglebone that has no GUI. To develop on this BBB, you could SSH in, write your code in the terminal, compile, and run - but you would miss out on all the great features of modern editors such as VSCode.</p>\n<p>With a little configuration we can setup a local VSCode instance to point to the remote BBB. We will be able to browse files/folders and create new ones, edit code with syntax highlighting, and more. It's like you're developing locally, but you're editing, compiling, and running remote code.</p>\n<h2>Setup</h2>\n<p>Today I will be working with a Macbook Pro w/ macOS Mojave. </p>\n<p>To check the kernel and OS on the Beaglebone you can <code class=\"language-text\">cat /etc/os-release</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">cat /proc/version</code>. You can see that we have Debian 9 and Kernel 4.14.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/54927/os-ver.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 21.503957783641162%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"OS and Kernel on BBB\"\n        src=\"/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/26fb4/os-ver.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/f723e/os-ver.png 188w,\n/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/d744b/os-ver.png 375w,\n/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/26fb4/os-ver.png 750w,\n/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/2a761/os-ver.png 1125w,\n/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/10439/os-ver.png 1500w,\n/static/669649c029cdf2a44d749e77dce7ed03/54927/os-ver.png 1516w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Hosts File</h3>\n<p>The hosts file is used to map IP addresses to friendly names. With it we can map the Beaglebone IP to a name we can remember and one that is easier to type.</p>\n<p>So, I <code class=\"language-text\">sudo nano /etc/hosts</code> and add an entry to map my beaglebone IP to the hostname <em>bbb</em>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/f722f/hosts.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.53920386007238%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"Editing the hosts file\"\n        src=\"/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/26fb4/hosts.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/f723e/hosts.png 188w,\n/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/d744b/hosts.png 375w,\n/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/26fb4/hosts.png 750w,\n/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/2a761/hosts.png 1125w,\n/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/10439/hosts.png 1500w,\n/static/ef2cb85415f0dac5767863429ededed4/f722f/hosts.png 1658w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Recall in the prior post we were able to ssh the IP of the BBB. Now, we are able to <code class=\"language-text\">ssh bbb -l debian</code> also. A bit easier to type, but also I don't have to try to remember the IP of so many different systems.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/69631/ssh-hosts.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.94134897360703%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH with a hosts file\"\n        src=\"/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/26fb4/ssh-hosts.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/f723e/ssh-hosts.png 188w,\n/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/d744b/ssh-hosts.png 375w,\n/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/26fb4/ssh-hosts.png 750w,\n/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/2a761/ssh-hosts.png 1125w,\n/static/94e6102a8c50e49096ca74cd09f0d806/69631/ssh-hosts.png 1364w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3>Code Editor</h3>\n<p>In case you haven't heard, VSCode is Microsoft's open source, no-cost, cross platform, extensible code editor. We will leverage that extensibility to connect to the remote BBB.</p>\n<p>Install VSCode from: <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">https://code.visualstudio.com/</a></p>\n<p>Install the Remote Development Extension too.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/b83b0/remote-dev-ext.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.146981627296586%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"Remote Development Extension\"\n        src=\"/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/26fb4/remote-dev-ext.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/f723e/remote-dev-ext.png 188w,\n/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/d744b/remote-dev-ext.png 375w,\n/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/26fb4/remote-dev-ext.png 750w,\n/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/2a761/remote-dev-ext.png 1125w,\n/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/10439/remote-dev-ext.png 1500w,\n/static/857adc017cd5c214798f1d84de98f537/b83b0/remote-dev-ext.png 1524w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>With these installed you can setup the connection to the BBB. In VSCode, open the <em>Command Palette</em> with <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + P</code> . At the prompt, start typing the word <em>remote-ssh</em> to filter the options. Soon you should see <em>Remote-SSH: Add New SSH Host...</em>. Select this option, and continue the prompts.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/20964/ssh-new-host.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.4331550802139%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"New Remote Host\"\n        src=\"/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/26fb4/ssh-new-host.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/f723e/ssh-new-host.png 188w,\n/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/d744b/ssh-new-host.png 375w,\n/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/26fb4/ssh-new-host.png 750w,\n/static/0955bd9c6aa22fcbf5ae0b0cba0a67bb/20964/ssh-new-host.png 1122w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Next, you will need to enter the command you want for connecting to your BBB. Note here I am using the hosts file entry for our bbb.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/16e33/ssh-conn-cmd.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26.02965403624382%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH Connection Command\"\n        src=\"/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/26fb4/ssh-conn-cmd.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/f723e/ssh-conn-cmd.png 188w,\n/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/d744b/ssh-conn-cmd.png 375w,\n/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/26fb4/ssh-conn-cmd.png 750w,\n/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/2a761/ssh-conn-cmd.png 1125w,\n/static/0e483a1e5b9efc91eea7c794af907e69/16e33/ssh-conn-cmd.png 1214w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>To open the remote connection to the host we just created, once again open the <em>Command Palette</em> and filter by beginning to type <em>remote</em>. Select the option for <em>Remote-SSH: Connect to Host...</em>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/a6ba0/ssh-conn-host.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26.513569937369518%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH Connect to Remote Host\"\n        src=\"/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/26fb4/ssh-conn-host.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/f723e/ssh-conn-host.png 188w,\n/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/d744b/ssh-conn-host.png 375w,\n/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/26fb4/ssh-conn-host.png 750w,\n/static/6979cdcae7149431b01d6d7c7348ec31/a6ba0/ssh-conn-host.png 958w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Select the bbb host we just created. This will connect to the remote host and open a new instance of VSCode. You will be asked for the SSH login password.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/a30c0/ssh-select-bbb.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.30769230769231%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH Select Host\"\n        src=\"/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/26fb4/ssh-select-bbb.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/f723e/ssh-select-bbb.png 188w,\n/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/d744b/ssh-select-bbb.png 375w,\n/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/26fb4/ssh-select-bbb.png 750w,\n/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/2a761/ssh-select-bbb.png 1125w,\n/static/9ad8d2bb1d3dff93881f02cd33993dd9/a30c0/ssh-select-bbb.png 1300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Now I can open a test app folder I created for this tutorial. It is located on the remote BBB at <code class=\"language-text\">~/code/test</code>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/9e4be/ssh-open-folder.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.121604139715394%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH Open Remote Folder\"\n        src=\"/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/26fb4/ssh-open-folder.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/f723e/ssh-open-folder.png 188w,\n/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/d744b/ssh-open-folder.png 375w,\n/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/26fb4/ssh-open-folder.png 750w,\n/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/2a761/ssh-open-folder.png 1125w,\n/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/10439/ssh-open-folder.png 1500w,\n/static/62c39fedce451768e54fefb1936db2bc/9e4be/ssh-open-folder.png 1546w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Opening VSCode's integrated terminal with <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL + ~</code> I can now build and launch the app remotely on the BBB.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/09666/ssh-rem-dev.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 51.67785234899329%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"alt text\"\n        title=\"SSH Remote Development\"\n        src=\"/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/26fb4/ssh-rem-dev.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/f723e/ssh-rem-dev.png 188w,\n/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/d744b/ssh-rem-dev.png 375w,\n/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/26fb4/ssh-rem-dev.png 750w,\n/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/2a761/ssh-rem-dev.png 1125w,\n/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/10439/ssh-rem-dev.png 1500w,\n/static/d0eb06150c6239a04fea88dec043fd1f/09666/ssh-rem-dev.png 1788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Summary</h2>\n<p>In this tutorial we added the Beaglebone to our hosts file, and configured VSCode to connect to the remote BBB. The purpose has been to make a nicer environment where we can develop code.</p>\n<p>For further reading you might consider cross-compiling for the BBB or setting up ssh keys for authentication in lieu of passwords.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2019-12-22","title":"Beaglebone Black - Getting Started Pt.2","tags":["beaglebone","linux","Embedded Systems"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3758389261744965,"src":"/static/c0875885476cd97344cb4f6ec233dfea/688c9/bbb2.jpg","srcSet":"/static/c0875885476cd97344cb4f6ec233dfea/688c9/bbb2.jpg 410w","srcWebp":"/static/c0875885476cd97344cb4f6ec233dfea/f778d/bbb2.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/c0875885476cd97344cb4f6ec233dfea/f778d/bbb2.webp 410w","sizes":"(max-width: 410px) 100vw, 410px"},"resize":{"src":"/static/c0875885476cd97344cb4f6ec233dfea/c4f3a/bbb2.jpg"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"pathSlug":"/Beaglebone-getting-started-p2","prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/Beaglebone-getting-started-p1","title":"Beaglebone Black - Getting Started Pt.1","tags":["beaglebone","linux","Embedded Systems"]}},"next":null}}}